Object.Field: Rate Plan Configuration Table The RATEPLAN table stores the rate plans to be configured by the network provider. Rate plans support the versioning concept and can have one ore more versions. Each rate plan version has a version date, a status value, a date of approval and an effective date. Each rate plan version of a rate plan refers to a network and a currency. - The rate plan versions are defined in the RATEPLAN_VERSION table. - The networks are defined in the MPDPLTAB table. Additional properties / attributes of rate plans: - A rate plan can be configured for prepaid or postpaid rating. - A rate plan can be configured by ST or PX. - It is possible to define a global rate plan to be used by MI. - It is possible to define a prerated Transferred Account Procedure (TAP) rate plan for each Home Public Mobile Network (HPMN) in the GSM market. - A rate plan can refer to an external rate plan that exists on the Intelligent Network (IN) platform. Example for user defined descriptions: - GSM-Global (GSMGL) - GSM-Global IOT (GSMGI) - GSM-External Carrier 1 (GEC01) Used by ST / PX: - Rate plans are configured in ST / PX and are stored in the RATEPLAN table. Used by MIH: - MIH is using global tariff model on assigning promotions. The Prepaid functionlality uses the global tariff model when assigning accounts for a balance overdraft. Used by RIH: - The incomming Usage Data Records (UDR) are rated by RIH corresponding to the rate plan (and its rate plan version) the customers contract refers to. Setup and configuration: - The RATEPLAN table contains configuration data to be entered by the user. In the standard baseline setup there are no pre-defined table entries available. More information: - EXTERNAL_RATEPLAN table comment - FORCURR table comment - MPDPLTAB table comment - MPULKNXV table comment - MPULKTMB table comment - MPUSPTAB table comment - RATEPLAN_AVAILABILITY_PERIOD table comment - RATEPLAN_HIST table comment - RATEPLAN_HIST_OCC table comment - RATEPLAN_VERSION table comment - REWARD_SERVICE table comment

Tariff Model (Rate Plan) Code The RATEPLAN.TMCODE attribute identifies the rate plan. The internal identifier is generated by the MAX_TMCODE application sequence. More information: - EXTERNAL_RATEPLAN table comment - FORCURR table comment - MPDPLTAB table comment - RATEPLAN_VERSION table comment

Description The RATEPLAN.DES attribute contains the description of the rate plan. Example for user defined descriptions: - GSM-Global (GSMGL) - GSM-Global IOT (GSMGI) - GSM-External Carrier 1 (GEC01) More information: - EXTERNAL_RATEPLAN table comment - FORCURR table comment - MPDPLTAB table comment - RATEPLAN_VERSION table comment
Short description of the BUSINESS_PLAN associated with the rate plan in a 1:1 relationship.

Tariff Model (TM) Global Flag The RATEPLAN.TMGLOBAL attribute flag indicates whether the rate plan (Tariff Model = TM) is a global one or not. - MI is the only online module which uses the global rate plan. It requires that the global rate plan contains Overdiscounting and Minimum Commitment as event-driven Value-Added Services (VAS). - The system does not check which services are appropriate services for this rate plan. Only one global rate plan can be defined for the entire system. If a new global rate plan should be specified, first the previous global rate plan muts be deselected. Then a new one can be assigned. Domain: Y := Yes, the rate plan (TM) is a global rate plan. N := No, the rate plan (TM) is a normal rate plan. Note: - Only one rate plan can be a global rate plan. More information: - MI online module documentation - ST online module documentation
Record Version The RATEPLAN.REC_VERSION attribute specifies the counter for multi user access. It is used for the optimistic locking method.

Prerated TAP Rate Plan Indicator The RATEPLAN.PRERATED_TAP_RP_IND attribute flag indicates whether the rate plan is a prerated Transfer Account Procredure (TAP) rate plan. - A prerated TAP rate plan can be set up for each Home Public Mobile Network (HPMN) in the GSM technology (market). Network operators can use prerated TAP rate plans to charge calls made by a home subscriber roaming in a foreign network (VPMN). Domain: Y := Yes, the rate plan is a prerated TAP rate plan. N := No, the rate plan is not a prerated TAP rate plan. More information: - ST online module documentation

External Rate Plan The RATEPLAN.EXTRNL_RATEPLAN_ID attribute specifies an external rate plan the current rate plan refers to. - The external rate plans are defined in the EXTERNAL_RATEPLAN table. More information: - EXTERNAL_RATEPLAN table comment

PDE Rateplan Flag The RATEPLAN.PDE_RATEPLAN attribute flag indicates whether the rate plan has been created by PDE. Domain: X := The rate plan has been created by PDE. NULL := The rate plan has not been created by PDE. Note: - Since RP1.2 the PDE module is not in use. More information: - PDE module documentation
X: Indicates provisioning to the external system. In the case rating is performed by an external system, contract changes must be provisioned to this external system.

The Flag is used for the data export and import control. The integer value is a bit masked value. The binary value can have 2 digits with - Bit 0: Import Case - Bit 1: Export Case Import-case: All entries, which are imported, are set to Bit 0=1, if using the command-line option -f. These entries are locked and cannot be changed by other applications. Otherwise the imported data are not marked (Bit 0=0). Export-case: All entries, which are flagged as Bit 1= 1, are ready for export. After exporting the flags are set back to 0.

This flag indicates the special usage of the rateplan. Domain: C = It is a CCP (content catalogue product) rateplan. The rateplan is only used within the content catalogue products, E = the rate plan is maintained by ECM L = Lean Product Offering NULL = others
